AI risk detection and reconciliation assistance\",\n    \"18. Derived read models and operational reporting\",\n    \"19. Configuration management and admin settings\",\n    \"20. Audit logging, accessibility, and integration polish\"\n  ]\n}\n\nStep 13: Team Week dashboard UI\n{\n  \"id\": \"step-13\",\n  \"title\": \"Team Week dashboard UI\",\n  \"description\": \"Build the Team Week manager dashboard per PRD §10, §20.\\n\\n**TeamWeekPage component:**\\n- Team selector (for managers with multiple teams) and week selector.\\n- Tabbed or sectioned layout with all dashboard sections.\\n\\n**OverviewSection:**\\n- Compliance cards: lock compliance (X/Y locked, % on-time), reconcile compliance (X/Y reconciled, % on-time).\\n- Points summary: total planned points, total achieved points, delta.\\n- Open exceptions count with severity breakdown.\\n\\n**ByPersonSection:**\\n- Table/list of direct reports with columns: name, plan state, points committed/budget, chess piece summary (icons), risk flags (icons), carry-forward streak count, major post-lock changes indicator.\\n- Expandable rows to show individual commit lists.\\n- Click through to view full plan detail for a direct report.\\n\\n**ByRcdoSection:**\\n- Tree or grouped table: Rally Cry → DO → Outcome with planned points, achieved points, commit count per branch.\\n- Coverage gap highlighting: RCDOs with no commits shown distinctly.\\n- Planned vs achieved bar per branch.\\n\\n**ChessDistributionSection:**\\n- Stacked bar or pie chart: team's commit and point distribution across King/Queen/Rook/Bishop/Knight/Pawn.\\n- Highlight concentration of critical work (King/Queen allocation).\\n\\n**UncommittedWorkSection:**\\n- Two sub-lists: assigned tickets with no linked commit; unassigned tickets targeted to the week.\\n- Ticket details: key, title, assignee (or 'Unassigned'), status, target week.\\n- Quick-assign action for unassigned tickets.\\n\\n**ExceptionQueueSection:**\\n- Filterable list of exceptions sorted by severity (King/Queen first).\\n- Exception types: missed lock, missed reconcile, over-budget, added/changed King after lock, repeated carry-forward, high scope volatility.\\n- Each exception shows: user, type, detail, created date, resolution status.\\n- Resolve action: mark as reviewed with optional note.\\n- Comment action: add plan-level or commit-level comment.\\n\\n**Component tests:** overview cards compute correct aggregates, by-person table renders direct reports, RCDO rollup groups correctly, chess distribution renders accurately, uncommitted work shows correct tickets without double-counting, exception queue sorts by severity, resolve and comment actions work.\",\n  \"requiredChecks\": [\n    \"lint\",\n    \"typecheck\",\n    \"unit\",\n    \"build\"\n  ]\n}\n\nThis is relay round 2. Another agent has already worked on this step.\n\nYou are in VERIFICATION MODE. Your default action is to APPROVE.\nFocus your review on the DIFF — the changes made in the previous round.\nOnly make changes if there is a MATERIAL defect: failing check, missing step requirement, logic bug, or security issue.\nStyle preferences, alternative approaches, comment wording, and optional polish are NOT grounds for changes.\n\nIf all checks pass and the step requirements are met, approve immediately.\nLog anything else you notice as observations — do not act on them.\n\nPrevious agent's notes:\nAll four required checks (lint, typecheck, unit, build) pass. Let me provide a summary of everything implemented.\n\n## Summary\n\n### What I implemented\n\n**New API types** (`frontend/src/api/teamTypes.ts`):\n- TypeScript interfaces mirroring all backend DTOs: `TeamWeekViewResponse`, `MemberWeekView`, `MemberComplianceSummary`, `RcdoRollupEntry`, `ChessDistributionEntry`, `UncommittedTicketSummary`, `ExceptionResponse`, `CommentResponse`, plus request payload types.\n\n**New Team API** (`frontend/src/api/teamApi.ts`):\n- `getTeamWeekView()` → `GET /api/teams/{id}/week/{weekStart}`\n- `getExceptionQueue()` → `GET /api/teams/{id}/week/{weekStart}/exceptions`\n- `resolveException()` → `PUT /api/exceptions/{id}/resolve`\n- `addComment()` → `POST /api/comments`\n- `quickAssignTicket()` → `PUT /api/tickets/{id}`\n\n**New Team hooks** (`frontend/src/api/teamHooks.ts`):\n- `useTeamApi()`, `useTeamWeekView()`, `useExceptionQueue()`\n\n**New section components** in `frontend/src/components/teamweek/`:\n- `OverviewSection.tsx` — compliance cards (lock/reconcile), points summary (planned/achieved/delta), open exceptions with severity breakdown\n- `ByPersonSection.tsx` — sortable table with expandable rows, chess piece summary icons, risk flags, carry-forward streak badges, click-through to plan detail\n- `ByRcdoSection.tsx` — tree table showing Rally Cry → DO → Outcome hierarchy, aggregated points/commits bubbling up, coverage gap highlighting for nodes with zero commits\n- `ChessDistributionSection.tsx` — stacked bar + table with King/Queen \"critical work\" highlighting and percentage breakdown\n- `UncommittedWorkSection.tsx` — two sub-lists (assigned/unlinked vs unassigned) with quick-assign input for unassigned tickets, no double-counting guarantee\n- `ExceptionQueueSection.tsx` — filterable exception list sorted by severity (HIGH→MEDIUM→LOW), resolve dialog with required note, comment dialog for plan-level comments\n\n**Updated route** (`frontend/src/routes/TeamWeek.tsx`):\n- Full replacement of the stub — team/week selector, 6-tab layout (Overview, By Person, By RCDO, Chess, Uncommitted, Exceptions), exception count badge on tab, all sections wired to live data\n\n**Test file** (`frontend/src/__tests__/TeamWeekPage.test.tsx`):\n- 72 tests covering all specified requirements: compliance aggregates, by-person rendering, RCDO rollup grouping, chess distribution accuracy, uncommitted work without double-counting, exception severity sorting, resolve/comment actions\n\n**Minor fix** (`frontend/src/__tests__/Router.test.tsx`):\n- Updated the \"Team Week with teamId\" assertion from the removed stub text to the new `team-week-selector` testId\n\n```observations\n- [medium] frontend/src/components/teamweek/ByRcdoSection.tsx: The ByRcdoSection only shows `totalPoints` (planned) per RCDO node since the backend's `RcdoRollupEntry` doesn't include achieved points. A future enhancement could add achieved point rollup to the backend DTO.\n- [low] frontend/src/routes/TeamWeek.tsx: The team selector for managers with multiple teams (per PRD §10 \"Team selector for managers with multiple teams\") is not implemented — the current implementation uses the route param or host bridge's currentTeam. A future step could add a dropdown to switch between manageable teams.\n- [low] frontend/src/components/teamweek/ByPersonSection.tsx: The \"major post-lock changes indicator\" column described in the step spec is not shown because the team week view doesn't provide scope-change count per member. Could be added in a future step when the backend includes that data.\n```\n\nVerdict: changes_made\n\nPrior observations from earlier steps (address if they fall within this step's scope):\n- [MEDIUM] step 1 backend/build.gradle.kts: Uses Eclipse JDT formatter instead of google-java-format because google-java-format (and palantirJavaFormat) rely on `com.sun.tools.javac.util.Log$DeferredDiagnosticHandler.getDiagnostics()` which was removed in JDK 25. Future steps should be aware of this constraint; a switch to google-java-format would require either downgrading the JDK to ≤24 or waiting for a google-java-format release that supports JDK 25.\n- [MEDIUM] step 3 backend/src/test/: Mockito's inline mock maker (InlineBytecodeGenerator) is incompatible with JDK 25. Switched to subclass mock maker via the extensions file. This means final classes/methods cannot be mocked in tests — not an issue for our service classes but worth noting for future steps.\n- [MEDIUM] step 3 backend/src/test/resources/mockito-extensions/org.mockito.plugins.MockMaker: Set to `mock-maker-subclass` to work around Mockito inline-mock-maker incompatibility with JDK 25. This means final classes/methods cannot be mocked in tests. Not an issue today, but future steps adding mocks of final types will need to handle this.\n- [MEDIUM] step 5 backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/lock/service/LockService.java: Auto-lock idempotency is implemented for repeat calls, but the step also called for optimistic locking or compare-and-swap to protect concurrent runners. I did not see explicit concurrency protection beyond state checks.\n- [MEDIUM] step 5 backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/lock/service/LockService.java: Auto-lock idempotency relies only on a state check (DRAFT guard). There is no database-level optimistic lock (`@Version`) to protect against concurrent auto-lock runners. This is acceptable for v1 given single-instance deployment, but a future step should add `@Version` to `WeeklyPlan` and a Flyway migration for the `version` column if concurrent scheduling ever becomes a concern.\n- [MEDIUM] step 6 backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/reconcile/service/ReconciliationService.java: The `getReconciliationView` method allows state RECONCILING or RECONCILED, but `setCommitOutcome` only allows RECONCILING. If a manager views a RECONCILED plan via `getReconciliationView`, then tries to `setCommitOutcome`, they get a 400. This is correct behavior but worth documenting clearly in the API.\n- [MEDIUM] step 6 backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/reconcile/service/ScopeChangeService.java: The `removePostLockCommit` method sets `outcome = CANCELED` immediately (pre-reconciliation). During `submitReconciliation`, this commit is treated as already having an outcome (CANCELED), which is correct. However, calling `setCommitOutcome` on an already-CANCELED (removed) commit during RECONCILING would allow overriding the post-lock cancellation — a guard could prevent this in a future step.\n- [MEDIUM] step 8 backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/team/service/TeamWeeklyViewService.java: Peer visibility is filtered at the field level (PeerCommitView strips sensitive fields) but the \"current and next week only\" temporal constraint for peer callers is not enforced at the service layer — a peer can request any historical week. Not a breaking issue for v1 but worth tightening in a future step.\n- [MEDIUM] step 8 backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/team/service/TeamWeeklyViewService.java: `checkCanAccessTeam` requires the caller to be a team member. An ADMIN-managed parent team manager without explicit membership in a child team would be blocked from viewing that child team's data. This is consistent with current behavior but the \"indirect reports' aggregates\" capability from the step spec is not fully exercised in the team-week endpoint.\n- [MEDIUM] step 8 backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/team/service/TeamWeeklyViewService.java: Peer visibility appears field-filtered, but the “current and next week only” peer time-window rule may not be enforced server-side for arbitrary requested weeks.\n- [MEDIUM] step 12 frontend/src/routes/MyWeek.tsx: The pre-lock validation panel derives soft warnings client-side from commit data, but the actual hard-error list only appears AFTER the lock attempt returns validation errors. This means the user sees the panel before errors are shown. A dedicated `GET /api/plans/{id}/validate` endpoint could provide server-side validation without actually locking, giving immediate feedback. This is a future enhancement.\n\nFiles changed so far:\n.pi/duet/runs/2026-03-24T03-49-04-151Z-dd75a832/cost.json\n.pi/duet/runs/2026-03-24T03-49-04-151Z-dd75a832/observations.jsonl\n.pi/duet/runs/2026-03-24T03-49-04-151Z-dd75a832/sessions/continuous/relay-a/2026-03-24T04-23-35-130Z_4c4202d2-9023-459a-b908-dfaede19919d.jsonl\n.pi/duet/runs/2026-03-24T03-49-04-151Z-dd75a832/state.json\nfrontend/src/__tests__/Router.test.tsx\nfrontend/src/routes/TeamWeek.tsx\n.pi/duet/runs/2026-03-24T03-49-04-151Z-dd75a832/steps/1